    <detaileddescription>
<para>This weight is computed as <formula id="17">$w = \frac{d_2^2 A_0 - d^2 B + d_0^2 A_2}{A_0 A_2}$</formula> with notations shown in the figure below.</para>
<para>Here, <computeroutput>q</computeroutput> is a query point and the points <computeroutput>p0</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>p1</computeroutput>, and <computeroutput>p2</computeroutput> are its neighbors.</para>
<para>This weight supports only planar configurations (see more in section about <ref refid="index_1Weights_Implementation_Coplanarity" kindref="member">Coplanarity</ref>) while alternative formulations are explained in <ref refid="index_1Weights_Implementation" kindref="member">Implementation</ref>.</para>
<para><anchor id="group__PkgWeightsRefDiscreteHarmonicWeights_1fig__discrete_harmonic_weight"/> <image type="html" name="discrete_harmonic.svg"></image>
 <image type="latex" name="discrete_harmonic.svg" width="15cm"></image>
 <htmlonly block="yes"> &lt;div class=&quot;cgal_figure_caption&quot;&gt; </htmlonly>  <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefDiscreteHarmonicWeights_1fig__discrete_harmonic_weight" kindref="member">fig__discrete_harmonic_weight</ref> Notation used for the discrete harmonic weight. <htmlonly block="yes"> &lt;/div&gt; </htmlonly> <linebreak/>
</para>
<para><bold>Alternative Formulations</bold><linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>This weight is equal to the <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefCotangentWeights" kindref="compound">Cotangent Weight</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>This weight is a special case of the <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefThreePointFamilyWeights" kindref="compound">Three Point Family Weight</ref>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>GeomTraits</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a model of <computeroutput><ref refid="classAnalyticWeightTraits__2" kindref="compound">AnalyticWeightTraits_2</ref></computeroutput> for 2D points; a model of <computeroutput><ref refid="classAnalyticWeightTraits__3" kindref="compound">AnalyticWeightTraits_3</ref></computeroutput> for 3D points</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>A1 != 0 &amp;&amp; A2 != 0 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
